# iFlow 01 - Order Intake to SFTP Staging

## Purpose

This integration flow receives customer order JSON from an external client through an HTTPS endpoint and stores the raw order file in an AWS EC2 SFTP inbox directory.

This is the first successfully tested integration flow of the OmniSync OrderHub project.

## Sender

Postman_Client / External Storefront

## Receiver

AWS_EC2_SFTP

## Adapters Used

- HTTPS Sender Adapter
- SFTP Receiver Adapter

## HTTPS Endpoint

/order_sftp_staging

## SFTP Target

Directory:

inbox

Resolved EC2 Path:

/home/cpiuser/inbox

File Name:

order_test.json

Append Timestamp:

Enabled

## Security Material

Credential Name:

sftp_cap

Credential Type:

User Credentials

Actual SFTP User:

cpiuser

## Important Configuration Note

In this CPI tenant, the SFTP receiver adapter uses the Security Material credential name in the User Name field.

Working configuration:

- SFTP Adapter User Name: sftp_cap
- Security Material Name: sftp_cap
- Security Material User: cpiuser
- SFTP Directory: inbox

The directory must be configured as `inbox`, not `/home/cpiuser/inbox`, because the SFTP adapter resolves the path relative to the SFTP user home directory.

## Flow Steps

Postman_Client  
→ HTTPS Sender Adapter  
→ Start  
→ Prepare Order File  
→ End  
→ SFTP Receiver  
→ AWS_EC2_SFTP

## Test Result

A JSON order payload was sent from Postman to the SAP CPI HTTPS endpoint. SAP CPI successfully transferred the payload to the AWS EC2 SFTP inbox directory.

Created file example:

/home/cpiuser/inbox/order_test20260709214045.json

## Sample Payload Stored in SFTP

```json
{
  "order_id": "ORD1001",
  "customer": {
    "id": "CUST101",
    "name": "Rahul Sharma",
    "email": "rahul@example.com"
  },
  "items": [
    {
      "sku": "P1001",
      "qty": 2,
      "price": 1200
    }
  ],
  "payment": {
    "status": "PAID",
    "mode": "UPI"
  },
  "shipping": {
    "city": "Bangalore",
    "pincode": "560037"
  }
}
